**************** To checkout ChibiOS *******************************

git submodule update --init --recursive

********** Dependencies for building firmware: ********************

First check you don't have any leftover lingering toolchains:

sudo apt-get remove binutils-arm-none-eabi gcc-arm-none-eabi

Now add the PPA for the latest toolchain:

sudo add-apt-repository ppa:terry.guo/gcc-arm-embedded
sudo apt-get update

For newer versions of Ubuntu (>13 or so) you'll want to check you get the right
version of the toolchain.  Run:

apt-cache show gcc-arm-none-eabi

Find the entry with a Maintainer of "Terry Guo" and copy its Version,
i.e. 4.9.3.2015q1-0trusty13, then run

sudo apt-get install gcc-arm-none-eabi=4.9.3.2015q1-0trusty13

replacing the bit after '=' with Terry's version number at the time of reading.

**************** To build and flash ***************************

make flash

*********** To toggle debugger board powering *****************

make power / make unpower
